  "body": "The OSD pod's hostname is currently being propagated to represent the `host` type buckets in the crushmap.  So when an OSD pod is recreated, a new randomly generated host bucket is created.  It should be consistent, ideally a name attached to the storage node like the hostname/nodeName.\r\n\r\nFor now here's how I work around this, by modifying the `osd` DaemonSet.  I set the hostname based on `nodeName` before running rookd.\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n# [...]\r\n      containers:\r\n      - command:\r\n        - /bin/sh\r\n        - -c\r\n        - 'sleep 5;\r\n          echo $(HOSTNAME) > /etc/hostname;\r\n          hostname -F /etc/hostname;\r\n          /usr/bin/rookd\r\n            osd\r\n            --data-dir=/var/lib/rook\r\n            --mon-endpoints=mon2=10.2.247.8:6790,mon0=10.2.136.140:6790,mon1=10.2.6.9:6790\r\n            --cluster-name=rookcluster\r\n            --data-devices=^sd '\r\n        env:\r\n        - name: HOSTNAME\r\n          valueFrom:\r\n            fieldRef:\r\n              apiVersion: v1\r\n              fieldPath: spec.nodeName\r\n# [...]\r\n```",
